USE OF FACILITIES AGREEMENT
This Use of Facilities Agreement (this “Agreement”) is entered into this 15th day of
March, 2023 (the “Effective Date”), by and between Last Mile Transmission, LLC, a Delaware
limited liability company (“Last Mile”), and Boswell Wind, LLC, a Delaware limited liability
company (“Boswell”). Last Mile and Boswell are sometimes referred to herein individually as a
“Party” and together as the “Parties.”
WHEREAS, Boswell will develop, construct, own, operate, and maintain a wind-powered
electricity generation project to be located on real property in Albany County, Wyoming (the
“Project”);
WHEREAS, Last Mile will construct and own certain electrical radial generation-tie line
facilities in connection with the Project, and any and all other facilities, equipment, and
improvements related thereto, as more particularly described in Exhibit A attached hereto (the
foregoing herein collectively called the “Gen-Tie Facilities”);
WHEREAS, Boswell and PacifiCorp have entered into that certain Standard Large
Generator Interconnection Agreement dated November 17, 2020, as amended, to permit Boswell
to interconnect with PacifiCorp at the Freezeout Substation;
WHEREAS, Boswell desires to use the Gen-Tie Facilities for the Project to interconnect
with PacifiCorp at the Freezeout Substation, to deliver energy and capacity to the PacifiCorp
Freezeout Substation, to receive backfeed power from PacifiCorp, and/or for communications
purposes for the benefit of the Project; and
WHEREAS, as the indirect owner of Boswell and Last Mile, Alterra Power USA Corp.
has determined that it is in the best interests of Boswell, Last Mile, and the Project for Last Mile
to grant Boswell the use of the Gen-Tie Facilities for the Project in exchange for Boswell (a)
contributing to Last Mile the funds necessary for Last Mile to construct the Gen-Tie Facilities and
(b) maintaining or causing the Gen-Tie Facilities to be maintained.
NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the promises, covenants and other consideration
set forth herein, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged, Last Mile and
Boswell agree as follows:
1. Term. The term of this Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and shall expire
upon decommissioning of the Gen-Tie Facilities (the “Term”). This Agreement may be
terminated by Boswell upon one hundred eighty (180) prior written notice, and such
termination shall be effective as of the date set forth in such notice.
2. Use. For the duration of the Term, Last Mile hereby grants to Boswell and its employees,
contractors, subcontractors, agents, licensees, successors and assigns the right to use the
Gen-Tie Facilities for the Project to interconnect with PacifiCorp at the Freezeout
Substation, to deliver energy and capacity to the PacifiCorp Freezeout Substation, to
2
receive backfeed power from PacifiCorp, and/or for communications purposes for the
benefit of the Project.
3. Payment. In consideration of the rights granted under this Agreement, Boswell shall timely
contribute the funds necessary in a manner designated by Last Mile for the timely
construction and operation and maintenance of the Gen-Tie Facilities.
4. Access. For the duration of the Term, Last Mile hereby grants Boswell and its employees,
contractors, subcontractors, agents, licensees, successors and assigns with reasonable
access to the Gen-Tie Facilities, to the extent of Last Mile’s rights, for Boswell’s use of the
Gen-Tie Facilities and in performance of its maintenance obligations under this
Agreement.
5. Notices. All notices, requests and communications (“Notice”) under this Agreement shall
be given in writing and be personally delivered or sent electronically (e-mail) to the address
set forth below:

If to Last Mile:

c/o Innergex Renewable Energy Inc.
1225, rue Saint-Charles Ouest, 10e étage
Longueuil (Québec) J4K 0B9
Attention: Legal
Email Address: legal@innergex.com

If to Boswell:
c/o Innergex Renewable Energy Inc.
1225, rue Saint-Charles Ouest, 10e étage
Longueuil (Québec) J4K 0B9
Attention: Legal
Email Address: legal@innergex.com
A Notice, if personally delivered, will be deemed to have been given and received on the
date of actual delivery and, if given electronically (e-mail), will be deemed to have been
given and received on the date sent, if sent during normal business hours of the recipient
on a business day and otherwise on the next business day. Any Party may at any time and
from time to time notify the other Party in accordance with this section of a change of
address, to which all Notices shall be given thereafter until further notice given in
accordance with this section.
6. Assignment. This Agreement and the privileges granted herein may be collaterally
assigned by either Party in connection with the financing of the Project or the Gen-Tie
Facilities or otherwise with the prior written approval of the non-assigning Party.
3
7. Entire Agreement; Amendments. This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement
between Last Mile and Boswell respecting the use of the Gen-Tie Facilities, and supersedes
all prior agreements, understandings, negotiations and discussions, whether oral or written,
of the Parties pertaining to the use of the Gen-Tie Facilities. This Agreement shall not be
modified or amended, except in writing signed by both Parties and no purported
modifications or amendments, including, without limitation, any oral agreement, course of
conduct or absence of a response to a unilateral communication, shall be binding on either
Party.
8. Governing Law. This Agreement shall be governed by and construed, interpreted and
enforced in accordance with the laws of the State of Wyoming.
9. Severability. If at any time any provision of this Agreement is determined to be illegal,
invalid or unenforceable by a court of competent jurisdiction, the remainder of this
Agreement will continue in full force and effect, and the Parties will promptly substitute
for the illegal, invalid or unenforceable provision a legal, valid and enforceable provision
that most closely approximates the original intent and economic effect of the illegal, invalid
or unenforceable provision.
10. Headings. The headings of the paragraphs of this Agreement are not a part of this
Agreement and shall have no effect upon the construction or interpretation of any part
thereof.
11. Counterparts. This Agreement may be executed electronically and in two or more
counterparts, each of which shall constitute an original, but all of which when taken
together shall constitute but one and the same agreement.

EXHIBIT A
GEN-TIE FACILITIES
The complete and operating radial generation-tie line to be designed, engineered and constructed
in accordance with that certain Standard Large Generator Interconnection Agreement dated as of
November 17, 2019, as amended, between Pacificorp, a corporation organized an existing under
the laws of the State of Oregon, and Boswell Wind, LLC and within Carbon and Albany County,
Wyoming and including, without limitation, access roads to upgrade and/or build, right of way
clearing, supply and installation of power poles and other structures, supply and installation of
conductors, insulators, and other hardware.
